Cell[TextData[{
 "Figure 6.1  Sobol\[CloseCurlyQuote] efficiency gain (Monte Carlo RMSE \
divided by Sobol\[CloseCurlyQuote] RMSE, at a fixed budget) versus dimension, \
for two budgets. In low dimension Sobol\[CloseCurlyQuote] is tens to hundreds \
of times more accurate per sample; the gain decays steadily as ",
 StyleBox["d",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " climbs and the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", "log", " ", "N", ")"}], "d"], TraditionalForm]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"12f3e1bb-7c9d-49ce-a271-bda81a2c1cdc"],
 " penalty bites, heading toward parity (grey line). The six-parameter PK \
problem of this post sits where the gain is still large \[LongDash] the QMC \
sweet spot."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{70, 70}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.35],ExpressionUUID->"0c8ceb9c-59a2-4083-9b8b-4ddbbd5d9761"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The practical lesson: QMC is most valuable in low-to-moderate dimension \
(say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"d", "\[LessEqual]", "20"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"c07a8911-2886-4af1-a76f-bad6a247c84d"],
 "), or whenever the integrand has low ",
 StyleBox["effective",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " dimension \[LongDash] a few directions that matter and many that barely \
do. Many Bayesian models, including this one, are exactly that."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"0253b915-530e-4106-bee9-502604ec0067"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["7.  Correctness: synthetic-truth recovery", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6eef6dc3-8221-4d8b-a075-7c0499fd2033"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A fast wrong answer is worthless, so we check that the QMC machinery \
recovers parameters we ",
 StyleBox["know",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ". We generate concentrations from a fixed \"true\" parameter vector plus \
noise, fit the same model, and ask whether the posterior brackets the truth:"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"a037e912-3117-4035-97c1-3d9833446476"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Generate synthetic data from known truth, then fit. *)
thetaTrue = {1.20, 2.50, 30.0, 1.80, 22.0, 0.45};
{synProblem, synConc} = SyntheticProblem[thetaTrue, 320.0,
   {0.25, 0.5, 1, 1.5, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16, 20, 24, 30},
   priorMedians, priorLogSD, 4242];
synDraws = PosteriorDraws[LDPoints[\"Sobol\", 8192, 6],
   LaplacePosterior[synProblem]];
Mean /@ Transpose[synDraws]                  (* posterior means *)\
\>", "Input",
 CellMargins->{{60, 30}, {6, 6}},
 FontSize->11,ExpressionUUID->"65db9c90-049d-420c-9ed1-01220ff7dffd"],

