Cell[TextData[{
 "Figure 7.1  Synthetic-truth recovery. Each parameter is shown as its \
posterior estimate divided by the true value, with a 90% credible interval; \
the red line at 1.0 is the truth. The well-identified parameters (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["k", "a"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "eecba584-ebb3-4046-97c5-bb90e7e597a3"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["CL",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["V", "1"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e6fd103c-79c8-4238-baef-704a35211b46"],
 ") land tight on the truth; the weakly-identified ",
 StyleBox["Q",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["V", "2"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "217627b1-b875-40a7-9513-0b8dab59171a"],
 " have wide intervals that still cover it. The method is correct, and it \
reports honest uncertainty where the data are uninformative."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{70, 70}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.35],ExpressionUUID->"e3cd9195-9fd4-44ba-8ca0-35033d86d975"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["8.  The practical pay-off", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"124cf0ef-5a83-4ef2-aebb-54c72ff29553"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Slopes are abstract; model solves are money. The question a practitioner \
asks is: ",
 StyleBox["to reach the accuracy I need, how many times must I run the \
forward model?",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " Inverting the fitted error laws \[LongDash] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"N", "\[Proportional]", 
    SuperscriptBox["tol", 
     RowBox[{"-", "2"}]]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "60fc359a-9e3f-4ca9-9343-391d35635ed2"],
 " for Monte Carlo, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"N", "\[Proportional]", 
    SuperscriptBox["tol", 
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "60577d59-a2b8-466e-be80-ec7b2f099561"],
 " for QMC \[LongDash] gives the count directly, and the ratio is the \
speed-up:"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"70e45742-fc28-4aa9-8260-edce5cd45cf1"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Forward-model solves to reach a target accuracy on E[C(6 h)]. *)
fitPow[e_] := Module[{c = Fit[Transpose[{Log[Nlist], Log[e]}], {1, x}, x]},
   {Exp[c /. x -> 0], Coefficient[c, x]}];
nForTol[e_, tol_] := With[{cp = fitPow[e]}, (cp[[1]]/tol)^(1/(-cp[[2]]))];
(* speed-up of Sobol' over MC at 0.1% relative accuracy *)
nForTol[rmsePred[\"MonteCarlo\"], 0.001 refPred] /
   nForTol[rmsePred[\"Sobol\"], 0.001 refPred]\
\>", "Input",
 CellMargins->{{60, 30}, {6, 6}},
 FontSize->11,ExpressionUUID->"dc3e61d6-5359-4dd1-b7ee-c9d1ff9e347c"],

